The shop is not 'aesthetically' pleasing, but Capriotti's is one of the great sandwich shops in town, for quality and price.
The beef and turkey is roast on the premises.
The sandwiches come in "small," "medium," and "large".
But do not be mislead by the label of 'small', since the small is actually 20 inches.
I usually am able to eat half and save the other half for the next day.
Their smalls are usually $10 total.
My personal favorites are  the "Bobbie" (turkey, dressing, and cranberry sauce, like Thanksgiving dinner on bread) and the Capistrami (Russian dressing, coleslaw, pastrami).
Capriotti's also has veggie varieties (i.e.
turkey substitute, which tasted like cold cut turkey).
There are about four to five in the valley that I have gone to, and none of them disappoint.
The one off Sahara just happens to be the closest to the Strip.
The next closest to the Strip is on Maryland pkwy, near the university.

I am in Vegas for work and it's hard to find less expensive lunch places that are good quality food.
Capriotti's is just what we are looking for with great flavored sandwiches for a low price.
Adding the peppers to the sandwich gives it great flavor.
They also have a chocolate bundt cake that is amazing.
There is not much seating though.

