Capriotti's is the best thing about Vegas, well at least for me.
If you're not familiar, Capriotti's is famous for serving up sandwiches from your shoulder to your fingertips (20 for $13), specifically the Capastrami which consists of pastrami, swiss cheese, Russian dressing and cole slaw.
Man-o-man this sandwich is good.
I love my sandwiches with crispy bread, but Capriotti's serves it up soft and saucy.
The hot pastrami is layered on the soft bread, topped with melted swiss cheese; the dressing is tangy and not too heavy; and the crispy cole slaw adds the perfect crunch to the sandwich.
I heard the Bobby is also a fan favorite at this sandwich joint.
The Bobby is described as Thanksgiving in a sandwich.
It consists of turkey, cranberry sauce and stuffing.
If you have money, please start your own franchise of Capriotti's in SF.
I'll definately be a regular.

